    <!-- chains -->
    <div class="w3-center" style="width:75%; margin: 0 12.5%">
        <p class="w3-left-align">Starting out, the player will be assigned either red or blue chains. The ranged players (healers, casters, and physical ranged positions) want to end up with blue chains to start and the melee players (dps and tanks) want to end up with red chains to start. To achieve this they need to swap out their chains by stepping into the center of the arena to trade out with the other mismatched players. Once this is achieved, everyone prepositions next to their orb. There are six orbs, with the melees sharing theirs and the ranged doing theirs individually. The DPS roles go West and Support roles go East. The following raid plans depict this motion.</p>
    </div>
    
    <br>

    <!-- raid plan imgs -->
    <div class="w3-center" style="width:80%; margin: 0 10%">
        <img src="./images/guide/raidplan1.png" class="w3-round w3-image w3-three w3-border w3-border-black" style="float:none; width:29%; max-width: 300px; min-width: 180px; margin: 10px 5px">
